The paper discusses the use of machine learning, deep learning, and artificial intelligence in biomedicine, which falls under the category of computational biology (cs.CB). The paper specifically focuses on the application of these techniques in digital health, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of multi-omics data, which is a subfield of quantitative biology (q-bio.QM) and systems biology (q-bio.TO). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CB, and cs.AI, followed by q-bio.QM and q-bio.TO.
